 (mainly southern): variant of   Thorn   1.","Irish: adopted for various Irish names containing an element meaning ‘thorn’. Compare   Thornton  .","Swedish (mainly <b>Thörne</b>): ornamental or perhaps topographic name from <i>törne</i> ‘rose bush’ or <i>thorn</i>, an ornamental spelling of <i>torn</i> ‘thorn bush’."],"variants":[{"name":"Thorn","meanings":["English and Danish: topographic name for someone who lived by a thorn bush or hedge (Old English, Old Norse <i>thorn</i>, Middle English <i>thorn(e)</i>, <i>torn(e)</i>). The name is also found in Sweden.","English: habitational name from a place called with Old English, Old Norse <i>thorn</i> ‘thorn bush’ (see 1 above), for example Thorne in Kent, Somerset, and South Yorkshire.","North German and Danish: topographic name for someone who lived near a tower, from Middle Low German <i>torn</i> ‘tower’."]},{"name":"Thurn","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Otto, Katharina, Milbert.","German: topographic name for someone who lived near a watchtower, or a metonymic occupational name for someone responsible for manning one, from Middle High German <i>turn</i>, <i>turm</i> ‘tower’. In some cases it may be a habitational name from any of the many places called with this word in the Rhineland, Bavaria, Austria, and Bohemia.","English (Warwickshire): variant of   Thorne  . This form of the surname is very rare in Britain and Ireland."]}]},{"name":"Allan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alan  , used mainly in Scotland and North America."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":29,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":38,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Sir Allan Thorne was born in 1186, in Thornton le Moors, Cheshire, England. He married Alicia Bickerstaffe in 1210, in Lancashire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1250, in Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 64."},"et":{"1186–1250":"1186–1250","1190–1263":"1190–1263","1212–1250":"1212–1250","1190":"1190","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1212":"1212","1210":"1210","1186":"1186","1263":"1263","1250":"1250","Thornton le Moors, Cheshire, England":"Thornton le Moors, Cheshire, England","Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England","Sefton, Lancashire, England":"Sefton, Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"1186–1250":"1186–1250","1190–1263":"1190–1263","1212–1250":"1212–1250","1190":"1190","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1212":"1212","1210":"1210","1186":"1186","1263":"1263","1250":"1250","Thornton le Moors, Cheshire, England":"Thornton le Moors, Cheshire, England","Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England","Sefton, Lancashire, England":"Sefton, Lancashire, England"},"fr":{"1186–1250":"1186–1250","1190–1263":"1190–1263","1212–1250":"1212–1250","1190":"1190","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1212":"1212","1210":"1210","1186":"1186","1263":"1263","1250":"1250","Thornton le Moors, Cheshire, England":"Thornton le Moors, Cheshire, Angleterre","Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Lancashire